<font class="pn-normal">As many of you know, I currently live on the tiny island of Guam, located about 800 miles north of the equator due north of Sydney.  What many of you may not know is that on Sunday, December 8th, 2002 the island was hit by SuperTyphoon Pongsona (pronounced: Pong-song-waa) with winds in excess of 160 MPH and torrential rains…<br />
</font><br>
<font class="pn-sub">Published Dec 12, 2002 - 02:55 AM</font>
